revno: 909
fixes bug: http://bugs.solfege.org/112
committer: Tom Cato Amundsen <tca@gnu.org>
branch nick: solfege.dev
timestamp: Sat 2008-12-27 00:07:22 +0100
message:
  Show an ok error dialog if latex or lilypond is not found on
  the PATH when we try to create the ear training printout.
  This fixes bug #112.
  
  We use subprocess.call instead of subprocess.Popen since it seems
  to handle exec not found better. And shell=False because sources
  say True is evil, and I don't remember why we did True earlier on.
------------------------------------------------------------
